Explanation: If a record is removed or deleted, the code does:
csharp
Copy
var deletedItem = (RemovedOrDeletedItem)change.ChangedItem;
var queueMessage = new CloudQueueMessage(deletedItem.RemovedItemId);
deleteQueue.AddMessage(queueMessage);
Thus, on a subsequent call (e.g., at line 3 or line 4) where the record appears as removed, a message is indeed placed in deleteQueue
